um concentration gradient. Moreover, simulations demonstrate that the\nsegregation of a Li-rich and a Li-poor phase during delithiation can drive the\ncracks to propagate. Results indicate that the model can capture the\nelectrochemical reaction on the freshly cracked surfaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Nov 2015 16:30:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-31"}
