ter are larger than\nsome of the previous estimates. As a consequence, we put new constrains on\nthese free parameters. An important result of our analysis is that our approach\nleads to new constraints on the parameter space of the chameleon models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Nov 2015 18:56:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 8 Jun 2016 00:16:42 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 10 Jun 2016 17:27:13 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 9 Nov 2017 12:36:12 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 5 Apr 2018 22:22:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-30"}
